  "description": "Saltharrow Transit Anchorage serves as the system’s principal spaceport, set on a hardened orbital platform aligned to the charted debris-belt lanes. Its architecture favors compact, ribbed hullworks and glare-shielded galleries designed to withstand the primary star’s hard white radiance. Gravitic-reference pylons and lattice-calibrated beacons dominate the superstructure, fixing approach vectors within Saltharrow’s pronounced gradients. Pressurized concourses connect modular berths, customs vaults, and sealed cargo galleries arranged for rapid turnover on deep-lattice schedules.",
